parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft position sensor can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to poor engine performance, reduced fuel efficiency, and potentially causing the engine to catch fire.
symptoms: The check engine light is illuminated
the engine is running rough
the vehicle is experiencing poor engine performance
smoke is coming out of the engine
oil leaks
and the vehicle is unable to pass smog tests.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The difficulty in obtaining recall repairs for the camshaft position sensor can lead to frustration and financial burden for vehicle owners, potentially causing them to delay or forgo necessary repairs.
symptoms: Dealerships are refusing to honor the recall
parts are unavailable
or the vehicle's VIN is not included in the recall
leading to owners being unable to get the necessary repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hose can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
brake fluid leaking from the front brake
burning smell from the front of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to obtain recall repairs can lead to continued operation of the vehicle with a known safety defect, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Difficulty in locating a dealership to perform the recall
dealership does not have parts available
dealership refuses to honor the recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft position sensor can cause the check engine light to come on, leading to engine problems and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving.
symptoms: Check engine light is always on
engine hesitation
engine stalling or shutting down while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front control arm bushing can cause the vehicle to vibrate, sway, or pull to one side, leading to loss of control, accidents, and uneven tire wear.
symptoms: Squeaking or grinding noise from the front of the vehicle
vibration or shaking while driving
vehicle pulls to one side
uneven tire wear
difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noise from the brakes
brake pedal goes to the floor
difficulty stopping
vehicle slides or pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt and engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Check engine light illuminates
